## IIS Deploy Commands

```powershell
# Deploy single app
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-DeployApp.ps1" -SiteName <name>

# Deploy all (teardown + iisreset + rebuild from all templates)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-RedeployAll.ps1"

# Uninstall single app (removes virtual app + app pool + firewall rules)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-UninstallApp.ps1" -SiteName <name>

# Diagnose broken app
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\Test-IISSite.ps1" -SiteName <name>

# Sync scripts/templates to servers after editing
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\_deploy.ps1"
```

Valid `-SiteName` values: `DedgeAuth`, `DocView`, `GenericLogHandler`, `ServerMonitorDashboard`, `AutoDocJson`, `AgriNxt.GrainDryingDeduction`, `AutoDoc`

## Deploy Templates

Location: `C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\templates\`

Naming convention: `<SiteName>_<InstallSource>.deploy.json`

Key fields: `SiteName`, `PhysicalPath`, `AppType`, `DotNetDll`, `InstallSource`, `InstallAppName`, `VirtualPath`, `ParentSite`, `HealthEndpoint`, `ApiPort`

## Deploy Steps (10-step process)

1. Teardown existing virtual app + app pool
2. Install files from staging (`Install-OurWinApp`)
3. Create app pool (set identity)
4. Create virtual application under Default Web Site
5. Verify/generate web.config (sets `ASPNETCORE_URLS`, `maxQueryString=8192`)
6. Set folder permissions (ReadAndExecute for app pool identity)
7. Create firewall rules (inbound + outbound for ApiPort)
8. Start app pool
9. Verify (app pool started, site started, virtual app exists)
10. Health check (HTTP GET to HealthEndpoint)

## IIS-RedeployAll Phases

1. **UNINSTALL** -- remove all virtual apps (apps first, root site last)
2. **IIS RESET** -- `iisreset /restart`
3. **DEPLOY** -- deploy root site first, then all apps from templates

