## Impact Rules

- **Changing DedgeAuth.Client** -- rebuild ALL consumer apps (`Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1`) then `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1`
- **Changing DedgeAuth wwwroot (CSS/JS/HTML)** -- rebuild DedgeAuth only; consumer apps fetch assets via proxy
- **Changing a single consumer app** -- rebuild that app only, then `IIS-DeployApp.ps1 -SiteName <name>`
- **Changing deploy templates** -- run `IIS-DeployApp\_deploy.ps1` to sync to servers, then `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1`
- **Changing IIS-Handler.psm1** -- commit to DedgePsh, run `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` to pick up changes

## Auth Flow

All consumer apps reference `DedgeAuth.Client` and use its middleware. DedgeAuth handles login, JWT tokens, session validation, tenant branding, user menus, and visit tracking. Consumer apps delegate to DedgeAuth via `AddDedgeAuth()` + `UseDedgeAuth()` + `MapDedgeAuthProxy()`.
